    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen the current window has the window-local option `winfixbuf` enabled, running `:tabdo wincmd =` unexpectedly creates an \n additional window displaying the same buffer. This is surprising because `wincmd =` should only equalize window sizes and should not create a new window. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nManual inspection:\n\nrun with `nvim --clean`, then run \n```vim\n:setlocal winfixbuf\n:tabdo wincmd =\n```\nAn extra window will show up.\n\nAlternatively, run `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua` with this minimal, and see window changes.\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"VimEnter\", {\n\tonce = true,\n\tcallback = function()\n\t\tvim.wo.winfixbuf = true\n\t\tvim.print(\"before\", vim.inspect(vim.fn.winlayout()))\n\t\tvim.cmd(\"tabdo wincmd =\")\n\t\tvim.print(\"after\", vim.inspect(vim.fn.winlayout()))\n\tend,\n})\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:tabdo wincmd =` should only equalize existing windows. It should not create an additional window, regardless of whether the current window has `winfixbuf` set.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.2.650\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.47.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
