            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "looks like the same root cause as vim/vim#14301.\n\nThe split comes from  `'winfixbuf'` unconditionally splitting at the top of `ex_listdo()`:\n\nhttps://github.com/vim/vim/blob/0d169a478cf37129042a9efb3300c41b13307a33/src/ex_cmds2.c#L481-L508\n\nNote that this behavior is confirmed by a test:\n https://github.com/vim/vim/blob/0d169a478cf37129042a9efb3300c41b13307a33/src/testdir/test_winfixbuf.vim#L2888-L2904\n\nI think `CMD_windo`/`CMD_tabdo` should skip that preemptive escape. However, I don't really know too much about these code paths. Hopefully this information is helpful for someone that wants to work on this.\n",
            "created_at": "2026-06-21T21:04:23Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40355#issuecomment-4763285695",
