        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Opened a PR for this: #40358 \n\nRoot cause is the one @barrettruth pointed to: `ex_listdo()` unconditionally\nescapes a 'winfixbuf' window by splitting before running the command. `:windo`\nand `:tabdo` only visit existing windows/tabpages and never change the current\nwindow's buffer, so that split is unnecessary. The fix skips the escape for\nthose two commands (buffer-changing commands like `:bufdo`/`:argdo` are\nunaffected, and `:windo buffer X` still errors with E1513 as expected).\n\nAlso covers the `:windo` case from vim/vim#14301.\n",
